The paper proposes an advanced traffic management system based on Hierarchical Interval Type-2 Fuzzy Logic model optimized by the Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO) method. This involves the use of artificial intelligence and optimization techniques to manage traffic flow, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of a traffic simulator (SUMO) also suggests relevance to Robotics (cs.RO) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the optimization aspect of the proposed system suggests relevance to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
